oai_dc:dc.dc:title: University of Denver Chamberlin Observatory
oai_dc:dc.dc:format: 1 item, (photograph), 8 x 10 inches, black and white
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Written on back of photographic print: "Bldgs - Chamberlin Observatory, 1913."

Exterior view of the University of Denver (DU) Chamberlin Observatory in Denver, Colorado. The observatory is on the National Register of Historic Places, and is named for Humphrey B. Chamberlin, a local land developer who donated $50,000 toward the project. The observatory was designed by Denver astronomer Herbert A. Howe, and the architect was Robert Sawyers Roeschlaub. Howe based the design on the Goodsell Observatory in Northfield, Minnesota. Two buildings are on the site, the main observatory, completed in 1894, and the smaller student observatory which was completed in 1891. A dirt road and prarie grass are visible in the foreground.
